div1.p: UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON NORTHERN DIVISION.
In the Matter of the Petition of HARRY GONG, alien, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus for YUT YOW.)

It appearing to the Court that Yut Yow, an alien, was not in charge of the Immigrant authorities, but had already been delivered to the ship, at the time that the Immigration Officer mentioned in the Petition was served with the Petition and Writ of Habeas Corpus, and that the attorney for the Petitioner is willing to have the cause dismissed;
IT IS HEREBY ORDERED, That the Writ of Habeas Corpus, heretofore issued, be, and the same is hereby dismissed, and the case closed.
IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON G O B-4-392
In the Matter of the Petition of HARRY GONG, alien, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus for YUT YOW.
FILED IN THE U.S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington, NORTHERN DIVISION FEB 4 1914
div1.ab: FRANK L. CROSBY, Clerk, By EML Deputy.
